VoteSim was written in Standard C (ISO/IEC 9899:1999) and should build
on any system with a compliant compiler. A Makefile is provided in the
source root directory of the release as a convenience.

To build this release of VoteSim on your system use:

    # make

The main executable will be built in the current directory. To run use:

    # ./votesim

To clean the directory of build files use:

    # make clean

A Doxygen configuration file is provided to generate the Doxygen
documentation for this release. To generate Doxygen documentation use:

    # doxygen Doxyfile

By default, documentation is generated as HTML in the doc/html directory
within the source root directory.
